text: right Oost- en West-Souburg is a former municipality in the Dutch province of Zeeland. It existed between 1835 and 1966, when it was merged with Vlissingen. The municipality included the villages of Oost-Souburg and West-Souburg. ==References== ==External links== * Map of the former municipality in 1868.
